news.title: Thane civic body presents Rs 5,645 crore budget for 2025-26
news.para: The civic body expects to garner Rs 841.58 crore from property and other taxes, Rs 650.8 crore from development charges and Rs 1,441.79 crore through GST and other grants.

news.title: Telangana high court halts land acquisition in Lagacherla and Hakimpet
news.para: Apart from suspending the ongoing land acquisition order, the judge sought counters from the state, revenue department and land acquisition authorities by April 7.

news.title: Pune civic body should monetise its land parcels, properties: Experts
news.para: Other means of monetary gains such as hoardings and flexes and utilisation of open spaces can be tapped, Sardeshmukh said. "For instance, roadside parking is free, even for commercial vehicles.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body's Abhay Yojana scheme collects Rs 42 crores as property tax
news.para: Under this Abhay Yojana, which started on February 22, the tax department of the Municipal Corporation succeeded in collecting property tax worth Rs 42 crores in 11 days.

news.title: Women home buyers surge by 14% in 2024: Report
news.para: As the report, residential transactions by sole women buyers grew by 14 per cent year-on-year, reaching 1.29 lakh transactions, up from 1.14 lakh.

news.title: Raipur civic body intensifies drive against property tax defaulters
news.para: Adding to the crackdown, the RMC issued a stern warning to The Living Room and Green Cafe, located on VIP Road, Amlidih.

news.title: Only 31% newly launched flats sold in Kolkata last year: Report
news.para: The ratio of new launch absorption was lower in Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR) at 36%, but it registered a whopping sales of 1,55,334 units.

news.title: Over 30 high-rise buildings in Noida switch to multipoint meter connections
news.para: Residents must pay a one-time charge of Rs 18,250 each for new meters to be installed by the discom. It can also be paid through EMI.

news.title: Trichy corporation forms climate action plan committee
news.para: Officials said transport, residential buildings, waste management, and street lighting emit large amounts of greenhouse gas (GHGs) in the city.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body delays interest waiver scheme; 477 properties sealed
news.para: However, this time, the corporation has still not announced the scheme, leading to uncertainty about whether it will be introduced. The chairman of the standing committee, Devang Dani, has not clarified whether the interest waiver scheme will be announced.

news.title: Tenants cannot challenge demolition of illegal buildings: Bombay HC
news.para: The court clarified that only property owners can contest such notices, rejecting a petition filed by tenants opposing the demolition of their premises.

news.title: Bombay HC clears path for redevelopment of 141 acres in Goregaon
news.para: The HC division bench of Chief Justice Alok Aradhe and Justice Bharati Dangre allowed a plea made in 2021 by Mhada to ensure redevelopment is done via private developers via a bidding process.

news.title: Maharashtra deputy CM moots TDR for redevelopment of buildings near Mumbai airport
news.para: The move will clear the decks for redevelopment of over 6,000 buildings in Vile Parle, Santacruz, Kurla and Ghatkopar, giving relief to 6-8 lakh residents, said officials.

news.title: Panchkula civic body plans to legalise some illegal colonies
news.para: The municipal corporation's proposal is to allocate 1-marla plots in Rajiv Colony, Indira Colony, Kharak Mangoli, Gandhi Colony, among other colonies.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM to launch infrastructure, IT projects in Noida
news.para: During the visit, the chief minister will lay the foundation stone for Microsoft's new campus, which is spread across five acres in Sector 145. He is also set to the IT firm MAQ's new building in Sector 132 and Sify's IT campus – also spread over five acres in the same sector.

news.title: Lucknow development body to conduct forensic audit of Ansal API projects
news.para: LDA appointed a private firm to conduct the audit, which will examine the builder's property records, public facilities and the status of internal and external development works.

news.title: NGT dismisses Bhubaneswar-based builder's appeal against SEIAA
news.para: SEIAA, on Feb 18, issued the show-cause notice to the city-based realtor for violation of norms prescribed in the Environmental Certificate (EC) issued to one of its mega housing projects being executed in Kalarahanga, Bhubaneswar.

news.title: Apartments’ registration in Odisha affected for lack of OC, allotees certificate
news.para: The OC, a document that proves a building is fit to live in, was originally introduced in 1993. It remained on paper until the advent of Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority (ORERA), but still, many buildings across the state do not have this very important certificate.
